node.text: Such a rad time with an awesome group of peoples. The @GridExperience definitely sets the bar (and sets it pretty high) for me when it comes to indoor karting. Combine that with a this crew of friends and fam: Jeremy McGrath, Sage Kotsenburg, Zak Hale, Davey Coombs (founder of Racer X), Zac Mertens (of Hoonigan Racing), etc. - plus Jett and Hunter Lawrence were two of the top three fastest of the night (same positions as they finished in the 250 Main of the Supercross race this past weekend!). Jeremy’s daughter (Rhowan) and my daughter (Lia) both had two of the top lap five times also (yep, we’re proud Dads!). Good times!

node.title: Rad time karting at The Grid Experience with friends and fam.

node.text: The @GridExperience’s indoor kart track is really amazing. It’s a half mile long, 3-level, has two banked corners, a drop - and the electric karts have a boost button! node.text: This weekend will be my first competitive drive in a Subaru since 2009. With only one proper day of testing before @AlexGelsomino and I show up this weekend to the @OlympusRally (3rd round of the @ARA_Rally Championship) it will be interesting to see how quickly I can get fully comfortable in it and run at full tilt. But so far, the car looks (livery by @ItsALiving) and feels (built and prepped by Vermont SportsCar) great! Check out this week's episode on my YouTube channel (link in bio) for the livery reveal, and to hear about all our plans for a wild year! #gravelslayingaction

node.text: Here’s another AINT CARE moment from the vault: @AlexGelsomino and I lost our front right side wheel midway through Stage 3 (of Oregon Trail Rally in 2013) due to a freak mechanical failure. We kept the hammer down and finished that stage, and then continued on to run another full stage on just 3 wheels, rather than settling for a DNF. We finished the race 2nd overall - all because we were able to drive through this #AINTCARE situation!

node.text: AIN’T CARE, rally cross example: after qualifying first, winning each of the heats, and leading the first 5 laps of the Final in the 2012 GRC race in Las Vegas, the ECU/control panel in my race car caught fire. I continued the race for as long as I could, but the fumes from the fire were starting to burn my lungs. I led and raced for as long as I could but eventually had to stop. I truly tried to AIN’T CARE as long as I could, but wasn’t willing to die for the win. 🤷‍♂️ #AINTCARE #pressonregardless

node.text: Lots of rain prior to The Rally in the 100 Acre Wood this year made for some very wet and rough stretches of the race stages. This video from Stage 12 is a sample of that at this year’s race in Salem, Missouri. @AlexGelsomino and I were fastest on this stage during the race, helping us secure 2nd place overall. Click the link to see the full on-board video from the entire 10.84 mile stage. #100AW

Legendary track builder Randy Mennenga (along with Fluff) - whom built the track last year - has finished some rad improvements to make our track even more world-class. node.text: More awards!! Hoonicorn Vs. The World was a wild ride - and the creative production that the Hoonigan staff and hosts put into it was amazing. So, it’s nice to be rewarded for that rad work with some nice new hardware! I got to race some insanely fast vehicles (McLaren Senna, Audi RS3 drag car, world’s fastest donk, etc) and put the Hoonicorn to the test - and now we have these Muse Creative Awards and Telly Award to show for that hard work! And BIG thanks to all the fans for watching and enjoying the @thehoonigans work. What was your favorite race in the series? #HoonicornVsTheWorld

Here is a closer look at the @tuthillporsche Porsche 911 that I will be racing early next year in the East African Safari Classic Rally, shot in the Tuthill shop in England. Love the details on this car: the bull bars, whale-tail wing, lights in the mirrors (to catch the attention of wild animals), etc. Really looking forward to racing this beautiful rally machine!! #Porsche911 #EastAfricanSafariClassicRally

-Fuel Cell: 100 liter with twin spare wheel capacity

node.text: Here it is: the @tuthillporsche built/prepared Porsche 911 I will be racing in the East African Safari Classic Rally! Looks amazing, right?? I love the look of these 911’s in their rally setups - and my 2021 livery art by “It’s A Living”  looks incredible on this thing. Unfortunately, due to updated COVID travel restrictions, the rally has been postponed to early next year. That’s life, but I will continue to prepare for this epic rally! #Porsche911 #EastAfricanSafariClassicRally

node.text: Rally racing can be dirty. Really dirty. Especially when the event gets wet and wild like last weekend’s Ojibwe Forests Rally. So, it’s nice to have a fresh clean rally car after every service - and @sonaxusa helps our team take care of that. #Sonax #OjibweForestsRally
